Description: A sealing from a document, the impression of which survives at the rear: one incomplete very large oval stamp with an uncertain pattern, perhaps a recumbent bull to right; below it is a raised line connecting to an edge-line; below again are retrograde Greek letters?. Adjacent are two oval impressions from another intaglio gem, of a largely naked running or squatting man to right, left hand extended, lowered right hand holding a plant (?) Unfired pale yellow-brown mud.
Curator's comments: Terracotta IV Donated: Egypt Exploration Society. Roman, probably second century AD.
Bibliographic references: Terracotta / Catalogue of Terracottas in the British Museum (3641)
